<p>Meanwhile, here are more examples of hypostomal attachment patterns in
 a variety of trilobites. <br>




  In addition to hypostomal patterns, you may notice other ventral cephalic 
 patterns typical of various orders including: <br>




  1) very wide rostrum (pink) in Redlichiida, 2) loss of rostrum in Phacopina, 
 3) ventral median anterior suture in Asaphida </p>




   
